TIRANA, Albania -- Two members of the US Congress met with Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano and Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami on Tuesday (17 February), and praised government efforts against terrorism.
Gil Gutknecht and Mark Kennedy, Republicans from the state of Minnesota, also discussed Albania's EU and NATO integration bids and progress in implementing reforms.
Also on Tuesday, Islami met with Maurizio Bussati, chairman of the International Migration Office, to discuss further co-operation.
They agreed on the need for enhanced collaboration to curb illegal immigration.
(ATA - 17/02/04)
